    {
      "name": "Reference - Sensitive Data Labels",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Available Classification Labels",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:4000/api/health",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "4000",
              "path": ["api", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Reference of all supported sensitive data classification labels:\n\n**Data Classification Labels:**\n\n1. **Personal-Identity** - Full name, national ID, passport, CCCD/CMND\n\n2. **Contact-Info** - Phone number, email address, home address\n\n3. **Financial-Info** - Bank account, credit card number, transactions\n\n4. **Health-Info** - Medical records, diseases, prescriptions, treatment info\n\n5. **Credentials** - Passwords, OTP codes, API keys, login tokens\n\n6. **Location-Info** - GPS coordinates, real-time location, movement history\n\n7. **Biometric-Info** - Fingerprints, facial data, retina scan, voice patterns\n\n8. **Non-sensitive** - No sensitive information detected\n\n**Compliance Standards:**\n- **HIPAA** - Healthcare data protection\n- **GDPR** - EU personal data protection\n- **PCI_DSS** - Payment card data security\n\n**How to use:**\n1. For direct text: POST to `/api/ml/classify` or `/api/ml/classify-by-standard`\n2. For Elasticsearch documents: POST to `/api/ml/classify-document` or `/api/ml/classify-documents-batch`\n3. To classify all documents in index: POST to `/api/ml/classify-all-documents`"
          }
